Show a specific session

Usage: normalize sessions show [OPTIONS] <SESSION>

Arguments:
  <SESSION>  Session ID or path

Options:
      --exact               Require exact/prefix match (disable fuzzy fallback)
      --jq <JQ>             Apply jq filter to each JSONL line
  -a, --analyze             Run full analysis instead of dumping raw log
      --filter <FILTER>     Filter messages by role/type: user, assistant, system, tool_use, tool_result, thinking
      --grep <GREP>         Search for pattern in filtered messages (requires --filter or shows all matching)
  -r, --root <ROOT>         Root directory (defaults to current directory)
      --errors-only         Show only error tool results (implies --filter tool_result)
      --format <FORMAT>     Force specific format: claude, codex, gemini, moss
  -l, --limit <LIMIT>       Limit number of sessions [default: 20]
      --ngrams <NGRAMS>     Extract common word sequences (ngrams) of length N (2-4)
      --case-insensitive    Case-insensitive ngram matching
      --json                Output as JSON
      --jsonl               Output as JSON Lines (one object per line)
      --pretty              Human-friendly output with colors and formatting
      --compact             Compact output without colors (overrides TTY detection)
      --output-schema       Output JSON schema for the command's return type
      --input-schema        Output JSON schema for the command's input arguments
      --params-json <JSON>  Pass command arguments as JSON (overrides CLI args)
  -h, --help                Print help
